FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://api.nustdevkit.com

# NUST LMS API
NUST Learning Management System API for developer integrations (Moodle AJAX wrapper).
Authenticate with your NUST LMS credentials via `POST /auth/login` to receive a bearer token, then call any operation with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. The NustDevKit gateway logs into the LMS on your behalf and manages the underlying session (cookie + sesskey) server-side, so you never handle the ephemeral sesskey.


## Authentication
This API uses JSON Web Tokens for its authentication.

The parameters that are needed to be sent for this type of authentication are as follows:
+ `JWTHeaderName`
+ `JWTAcquireURL`
+ `JWTDestroyURL`

# Group Authentication

Exchange NUST LMS credentials for a gateway bearer token

## Auth Login [/auth/login]

### login [POST]
Authenticates against NUST LMS on your behalf and returns a gateway JWT. The LMS session (cookie + sesskey) is created and held server-side; use the returned token as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` for every other operation.

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (LoginRequest)



+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Authentication succeeded; bearer token issued.

    + Attributes (TokenResponse)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Invalid LMS credentials.

    + Attributes (Auth Login 401 Error1)





# Group Courses

Course listing and enrollment operations

## Service Core Course Get Recent Courses [/service/core_course_get_recent_courses{?limit}]

### getCoreRecentCourses [GET]
Returns the courses the authenticated user has accessed most recently, ordered by last access time.
Moodle method: `core_course_get_recent_courses`
+ Parameters
    + limit (number, optional) -

        Maximum number of courses to return.

        + Default: 10

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        List of recently accessed courses ordered by last access.

    + Attributes (array[RecentCourse])



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)




## Service Core Course Get Enrolled Courses By Timeline Classification [/service/core_course_get_enrolled_courses_by_timeline_classification{?offset,limit,classification,sort}]

### getEnrolledCoursesByTimeline [GET]
Returns all courses the user is enrolled in, filtered by timeline classification and sorted by a chosen field. Supports pagination via offset.
Moodle method: `core_course_get_enrolled_courses_by_timeline_classification`
+ Parameters
    + offset (number, optional) -

        Zero-based pagination offset.

        + Default: 0
    + limit (number, optional) -

        Maximum number of courses to return.

        + Default: 50
    + classification (enum[string], required)

        Timeline classification filter for enrolled courses.

        + Members
            + `all` 
            + `inprogress` 
            + `past` 
            + `future` 
            + `favourites` 
            + `hidden` 
            + `allincludinghidden` 

    + sort (enum[string], required)

        Field used to sort enrolled course results.

        + Members
            + `fullname` 
            + `shortname` 
            + `id` 
            + `idnumber` 
            + `timeaccess` 


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Paginated list of enrolled courses.

    + Attributes (EnrolledCoursesResponse)



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)




## Service Core Course Get Contents [/service/core_course_get_contents{?courseid}]

### getCourseContents [GET]
Returns the full content structure of a course — its sections (weeks/topics) and the modules within them (files, folders, pages, URLs, assignments, and other activities), including metadata for each uploaded file. This is the data the course page itself is built from.
Note: file URLs point at Moodle's `pluginfile.php` and require authentication (a webservice token or the active session) to download — the URL alone is not publicly fetchable.
Moodle method: `core_course_get_contents`
+ Parameters
    + courseid (number, required)

        ID of the course whose contents to retrieve.


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Course sections, each with its modules and their uploaded files.

    + Attributes (array[CourseSection])



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)





# Group Calendar

Calendar operations. On NUST LMS, these "action events" are how deadlines are surfaced — assignment, lab, quiz, and other submission due dates each appear as a calendar event on the day the work must be submitted.


## Service Core Calendar Get Action Events By Timesort [/service/core_calendar_get_action_events_by_timesort{?limitnum,timesortfrom,timesortto,aftereventid}]

### getCalendarEventsByTimesort [GET]
Returns action events (deadlines) across all enrolled courses, ordered by their sort timestamp. On NUST LMS these are submission due dates for assignments, labs, quizzes, and similar dated activities. Use `timesortfrom` to filter to upcoming deadlines only.
Moodle method: `core_calendar_get_action_events_by_timesort`
+ Parameters
    + limitnum (number, required)

        Maximum number of events to return (e.g. 20 for one page of results).

        + Sample: 20
    + timesortfrom (number, required)

        Unix timestamp (seconds since epoch). Only events with a sort time at or after this value are returned. Pass `0` for no lower bound (all upcoming and past events). To see only upcoming deadlines, pass the current epoch time (e.g. the output of `Date.now() / 1000 | 0` in JS or `int(time.time())` in Python).

        + Sample: 0
    + timesortto (number, optional)

        Only return events with timesort <= this Unix timestamp.

    + aftereventid (number, optional)

        Return events whose ID is greater than this value (cursor pagination).


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Calendar events sorted by timesort.

    + Attributes (CalendarEventsResponse)



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)




## Service Core Calendar Get Action Events By Course [/service/core_calendar_get_action_events_by_course{?courseid,timesortfrom,timesortto,aftereventid,limitnum}]

### getCalendarEventsByCourse [GET]
Returns all action events (deadlines) for a single course — assignment, lab, and quiz submission due dates, and other dated activities.
Moodle method: `core_calendar_get_action_events_by_course`
+ Parameters
    + courseid (number, required)

        ID of the course to fetch events for.

    + timesortfrom (number, optional)

        Only return events with timesort >= this Unix timestamp.

    + timesortto (number, optional)

        Only return events with timesort <= this Unix timestamp.

    + aftereventid (number, optional)

        Cursor-based pagination — return events after this event ID.

    + limitnum (number, optional)

        Maximum number of events to return.


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Calendar events for the specified course.

    + Attributes (CalendarEventsResponse)



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)





# Group Account

Your identity and account/site information

## Service Core Webservice Get Site Info [/service/core_webservice_get_site_info]

### getSiteInfo [GET]
Returns your identity (user ID, username, full name, profile picture) and basic site information. Use this to discover your own `userid` — required by other endpoints such as popup notifications (`useridto`).
Moodle method: `core_webservice_get_site_info`

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Your account and site information.

    + Attributes (SiteInfo)



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)





# Group Notifications

Notification retrieval operations

## Service Message Popup Get Popup Notifications [/service/message_popup_get_popup_notifications{?useridto,limit,offset}]

### getPopupNotifications [GET]
Returns the most recent popup notifications sent to a user, with support for pagination. Also returns the total count of unread notifications.
Moodle method: `message_popup_get_popup_notifications`
+ Parameters
    + useridto (string, required)

        ID of the recipient user (yourself), passed as a string. Get your numeric user ID from `GET /service/core_webservice_get_site_info`.

    + limit (number, required)

        Maximum number of notifications to return.

    + offset (number, optional) -

        Pagination offset.

        + Default: 0

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        Popup notifications and total unread count.

    + Attributes (PopupNotificationsResponse)



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        Bad request or Moodle exception.

    + Attributes (MoodleError)





# Data Structures

## LoginRequest (object)
NUST LMS credentials used to obtain a gateway bearer token.

### Properties
+ `username`: `johndoe.bscs23seecs` (string, required) - NUST LMS username.
+ `password` (string, required) - NUST LMS password.


## TokenResponse (object)
Bearer token issued by the gateway after a successful login.

### Properties
+ `access_token` (string, required) - JWT to send as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on subsequent requests.
+ `token_type`: `bearer` (string, required) 


## MoodleWarning (object)
A non-fatal warning returned alongside a successful response.

### Properties
+ `item` (string, optional) - Item identifier related to the warning; empty string if not applicable.
+ `itemid`: `0` (number, optional) - Numeric item ID related to the warning; 0 if not applicable.
+ `warningcode` (string, optional) - Machine-readable warning code; empty string if no code.
+ `message` (string, optional) - Human-readable warning description.


## SiteInfo (object)
Your identity plus basic site information, from Moodle's site-info call. The `userid` here is what other endpoints need (e.g. it is the `useridto` for popup notifications).

### Properties
+ `userid`: `234567` (number, required) - Your numeric Moodle user ID.
+ `username`: `johndoe.bscs23seecs` (string, required) - Your login username.
+ `firstname`: `John` (string, optional) - Your first name.
+ `lastname`: `Doe` (string, optional) - Your last name.
+ `fullname`: `John Doe` (string, required) - Your full display name.
+ `userpictureurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/pluginfile.php/1583361/user/icon/moove/f1` (string, optional) - URL of your profile picture.
+ `lang`: `en` (string, optional) - Your preferred interface language code.
+ `sitename`: `NUST LMS` (string, required) - Name of the LMS site.
+ `siteurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal` (string, optional) - Base URL of the LMS site.
+ `release`: `4.1.2` (string, optional) - Moodle release/version string of the site.


## MoodleError (object)
Error returned by the LMS on a failed operation.

### Properties
+ `errorcode`: `invalidrecord` (string, optional) - Machine-readable error code identifier.
+ `message`: `Can't find data record in database table.` (string, optional) - Human-readable error description.
+ `link` (string, optional) - Redirect URL for the user; empty string if not applicable.
+ `moreinfourl` (string, optional) - URL to additional error documentation; empty string if not available.
+ `debuginfo` (string, optional) - Additional debug information; empty string when not in debug mode.


## Course (object)
An enrolled course.

### Properties
+ `id`: `49900` (number, required) - Unique course identifier.
+ `fullname`: `CS-212 Object Oriented Programming BSCS-13 2K23 ABC` (string, required) - Full display name of the course.
+ `shortname`: `CS-212-Sp'24 BSCS-13 2K23 ABC` (string, required) - Short course code or abbreviated name.
+ `idnumber` (string, required) - Institution-assigned course ID number; empty string if not set.
+ `summary` (string, required) - HTML summary of the course.
+ `summaryformat`: `1` (number, required) - Format of the summary field (1 = HTML).
+ `startdate`: `1706468400` (number, required) - Course start date as Unix timestamp.
+ `enddate`: `1717362000` (number, required) - Course end date as Unix timestamp. 0 means no end date.
+ `visible`: `true` (boolean, required) - Whether the course is visible to enrolled students.
+ `fullnamedisplay`: `CS-212 Object Oriented Programming BSCS-13 2K23 ABC` (string, required) - Display name of the course (may differ from fullname for context).
+ `viewurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/course/view.php?id=49900` (string, required) - URL to the course page on the LMS portal.
+ `progress`: `21` (number, required) - Student's completion progress as a percentage.
+ `hasprogress`: `true` (boolean, required) - Whether completion tracking is enabled for this course.
+ `isfavourite`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the user has marked this course as a favourite.
+ `hidden`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the user has hidden this course from their dashboard.
+ `showshortname`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the short name is displayed alongside the full name.
+ `coursecategory`: `2nd Semester (SP-2024)` (string, required) - Name of the category this course belongs to.


## RecentCourseFields (object)
Additional fields specific to recently accessed courses.

### Properties
+ `timeaccess`: `1781632422` (number, required) - Unix timestamp of the user's most recent access to this course.


## RecentCourse (object)
A recently accessed course, extending Course with the last-access timestamp.

### Properties
+ `id`: `49900` (number, required) - Unique course identifier.
+ `fullname`: `CS-212 Object Oriented Programming BSCS-13 2K23 ABC` (string, required) - Full display name of the course.
+ `shortname`: `CS-212-Sp'24 BSCS-13 2K23 ABC` (string, required) - Short course code or abbreviated name.
+ `idnumber` (string, required) - Institution-assigned course ID number; empty string if not set.
+ `summary` (string, required) - HTML summary of the course.
+ `summaryformat`: `1` (number, required) - Format of the summary field (1 = HTML).
+ `startdate`: `1706468400` (number, required) - Course start date as Unix timestamp.
+ `enddate`: `1717362000` (number, required) - Course end date as Unix timestamp. 0 means no end date.
+ `visible`: `true` (boolean, required) - Whether the course is visible to enrolled students.
+ `fullnamedisplay`: `CS-212 Object Oriented Programming BSCS-13 2K23 ABC` (string, required) - Display name of the course (may differ from fullname for context).
+ `viewurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/course/view.php?id=49900` (string, required) - URL to the course page on the LMS portal.
+ `progress`: `21` (number, required) - Student's completion progress as a percentage.
+ `hasprogress`: `true` (boolean, required) - Whether completion tracking is enabled for this course.
+ `isfavourite`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the user has marked this course as a favourite.
+ `hidden`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the user has hidden this course from their dashboard.
+ `showshortname`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the short name is displayed alongside the full name.
+ `coursecategory`: `2nd Semester (SP-2024)` (string, required) - Name of the category this course belongs to.
+ `timeaccess`: `1781632422` (number, required) - Unix timestamp of the user's most recent access to this course.


## EnrolledCoursesResponse (object)
Paginated enrolled-courses response.

### Properties
+ `courses` (array[Course], required) - List of enrolled courses for the current page.
+ `nextoffset`: `29` (number, required) - Offset to pass on the next page request; -1 when no further pages exist.


## CourseContentFile (object)
A single file (or link) uploaded inside a course module.

### Properties
+ `type`: `file` (string, required) - Content type, e.g. 'file' or 'url'.
+ `filename`: `Lecture01-Intro.pdf` (string, required) - Name of the file (or title of the link).
+ `filepath`: `/` (string, optional, nullable) - Folder path within the module; "/" for the module root.
+ `filesize`: `482133` (number, optional) - File size in bytes (0 for links).
+ `fileurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/webservice/pluginfile.php/123456/mod_resource/content/1/Lecture01-Intro.pdf` (string, required) - Moodle pluginfile.php URL for the content. Downloading the bytes requires authentication (a webservice token or the active session); the URL alone is not publicly fetchable.
+ `mimetype`: `application/pdf` (string, optional, nullable) - MIME type of the file when applicable.
+ `timemodified`: `1707745200` (number, optional) - Unix timestamp of the last modification.


## CourseModule (object)
An item on the course page — an activity or resource (file, page, URL, assignment, ...).

### Properties
+ `id`: `987654` (number, required) - Course module ID (cmid).
+ `name`: `Lecture 01 — Introduction` (string, required) - Display name of the module.
+ `modname`: `resource` (string, required) - Module type, e.g. 'resource' (file), 'folder', 'url', 'page', 'label', 'assign', 'quiz', 'forum'.
+ `modplural`: `Files` (string, optional) - Human-readable plural label for the module type.
+ `instance`: `45678` (number, optional) - Instance ID of the activity within its module type.
+ `description`: `<p>Course introduction and logistics.</p>` (string, optional, nullable) - HTML description/intro for the module, when present.
+ `visible`: `1` (number, optional) - Whether the module is visible (1) or hidden (0).
+ `uservisible`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Whether the module is visible to the current user.
+ `url`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/mod/resource/view.php?id=987654` (string, optional, nullable) - Link to open the activity/resource, when applicable.
+ `modicon`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/theme/image.php/moove/core/1/f/pdf` (string, optional, nullable) - URL of the module's type icon.
+ `contents` (array[CourseContentFile], optional) - Uploaded files/links for this module (present for resource/folder modules).


## CourseSection (object)
A section (week/topic) of the course, containing its modules.

### Properties
+ `id`: `33445` (number, required) - Section ID.
+ `name`: `Week 1` (string, required) - Section title (e.g. a week or topic name).
+ `section`: `1` (number, required) - Zero-based section number within the course.
+ `visible`: `1` (number, optional) - Whether the section is visible (1) or hidden (0).
+ `summary`: `<p>Introduction and course overview.</p>` (string, optional, nullable) - HTML summary shown at the top of the section.
+ `summaryformat`: `1` (number, optional) - Moodle text format of the summary (1 = HTML).
+ `uservisible`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Whether the section is visible to the current user.
+ `modules` (array[CourseModule], required) - The activities and resources in this section.


## EventIcon (object)
Icon metadata for a calendar event.

### Properties
+ `key`: `icon` (string, required) - Icon key name used to locate the icon asset.
+ `component`: `assign` (string, required) - Moodle component that owns the icon (e.g., 'assign').
+ `alttext`: `Activity event` (string, required) - Accessible alt text for the icon image.


## EventSubscription (object)
Subscription display settings for a calendar event.

### Properties
+ `displayeventsource`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether to display the event source label on the calendar.


## EventAction (object)
Primary action button metadata for a calendar event.

### Properties
+ `name`: `Add submission` (string, required) - Display label for the primary action button.
+ `url`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/mod/assign/view.php?id=999404&action=editsubmission` (string, required) - URL the user should navigate to in order to perform the action.
+ `itemcount`: `1` (number, required) - Number of items associated with this action.
+ `actionable`: `true` (boolean, required) - Whether the action can currently be taken by the user.
+ `showitemcount`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether to display the item count alongside the action label.


## CalendarEvent (object)
A calendar action event. On NUST LMS these represent deadlines — the due date for an assignment, lab, quiz, or other submission tied to a course activity.

### Properties
+ `id`: `149885` (number, required) - Unique calendar event identifier.
+ `name`: `Lab 1 BSCS 13C is due` (string, required) - Display name of the calendar event.
+ `description`: `<p dir="ltr">Lab 1 BSCS 13C<br /></p>` (string, required) - HTML description body of the event.
+ `descriptionformat`: `1` (number, required) - Text format of the description (1 = HTML).
+ `location` (string, required) - Physical or virtual location of the event; empty string if not specified.
+ `categoryid` (number, optional, nullable) - Course category ID; null if not a category event.
+ `groupid` (number, optional, nullable) - Group ID if the event is group-specific; null otherwise.
+ `userid` (number, optional, nullable) - User ID if the event is user-specific; null otherwise.
+ `repeatid` (number, optional, nullable) - ID of the repeat group for recurring events; null if not recurring.
+ `eventcount` (number, optional, nullable) - Total number of events in the repeat group; null if not applicable.
+ `component`: `mod_assign` (string, required) - Moodle component that created the event (e.g., 'mod_assign').
+ `modulename`: `assign` (string, required) - Short name of the Moodle activity module (e.g., 'assign').
+ `instance`: `999404` (number, required) - The course module instance ID.
+ `eventtype`: `due` (string, required) - Type of the event (e.g., 'due', 'open', 'close').
+ `timestart`: `1706900340` (number, required) - Event start time as Unix timestamp.
+ `timeduration`: `0` (number, required) - Duration in seconds; 0 for point-in-time events.
+ `timesort`: `1706900340` (number, required) - Sort timestamp used for ordering events.
+ `visible` (number, required) - Visibility flag for a calendar event. 1 means the event is visible; 0 means it is hidden.
+ `timemodified`: `1779088440` (number, required) - Last modification time as Unix timestamp.
+ `icon` (EventIcon, required) - Icon metadata for a calendar event.
+ `course` (Course, required) - An enrolled course.
+ `subscription` (EventSubscription, required) - Subscription display settings for a calendar event.
+ `canedit`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the current user can edit this event.
+ `candelete`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the current user can delete this event.
+ `deleteurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/calendar/delete.php?id=149885&course=49900` (string, required) - URL to delete this calendar event.
+ `editurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/course/mod.php?update=999404&return=1&sesskey=XXXX` (string, required) - URL to edit the underlying course module associated with this event.
+ `viewurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/calendar/view.php?view=day&course=49900&time=1706900340` (string, required) - URL to view this event on the calendar.
+ `formattedtime`: `<span class="dimmed_text">Friday, 2 February, 11:59 PM</span>` (string, required) - HTML-formatted human-readable event time string.
+ `isactionevent`: `true` (boolean, required) - Whether this is an action event requiring user interaction.
+ `iscourseevent`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether this event is associated with a specific course.
+ `iscategoryevent`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether this event is associated with a course category.
+ `groupname` (string, optional, nullable) - Name of the group for group-specific events; null otherwise.
+ `normalisedeventtype`: `course` (string, required) - Normalised event type identifier used for display grouping.
+ `normalisedeventtypetext`: `Course event` (string, required) - Human-readable label for the normalised event type.
+ `action` (EventAction, optional) - Primary action button metadata for a calendar event.
+ `url`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/mod/assign/view.php?id=999404` (string, required) - Direct URL to the course activity associated with this event.


## CalendarEventsResponse (object)
A list of calendar events with pagination boundary IDs.

### Properties
+ `events` (array[CalendarEvent], required) - List of calendar action events for the current result set.
+ `firstid`: `149885` (number, required) - Event ID of the first item in the result set.
+ `lastid`: `151886` (number, required) - Event ID of the last item in the result set.


## Notification (object)
A popup notification message delivered to a user.

### Properties
+ `id`: `4857819` (number, required) - Unique notification identifier.
+ `useridfrom`: `234567` (number, required) - User ID of the sender.
+ `useridto`: `123456` (number, required) - User ID of the recipient.
+ `subject`: `CS-101 Introduction to Computing: Lab 3 Submission Deadline` (string, required) - Subject line of the notification.
+ `shortenedsubject`: `CS-101 Introduction to Computing: Lab 3 Submission Deadline` (string, required) - Shortened version of the notification subject for compact display.
+ `text`: `<p>John Doe posted in CS-101 Introduction to Computing...</p>` (string, required) - Short HTML excerpt of the notification.
+ `fullmessage` (string, required) - Full plain-text body of the notification.
+ `fullmessageformat`: `2` (number, required) - Format identifier for fullmessagehtml (2 = Markdown source).
+ `fullmessagehtml` (string, required) - Full HTML body of the notification email.
+ `smallmessage`: `John Doe posted in CS-101 Introduction to Computing...` (string, required) - Short plain-text preview of the notification.
+ `contexturl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/mod/forum/discuss.php?d=41767#p52342` (string, required) - URL to the relevant context for this notification (e.g., a forum post).
+ `contexturlname`: `Lab Sessional Finalization - (DL - Section D & E)` (string, required) - Human-readable label for the context URL link.
+ `timecreated`: `1780045085` (number, required) - Unix timestamp when the notification was created.
+ `timecreatedpretty`: `19 days ago` (string, required) - Human-readable relative time string (e.g., '19 days ago').
+ `timeread` (number, optional, nullable) - Unix timestamp when the notification was read; null if unread.
+ `read`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the notification has been read by the recipient.
+ `deleted`: `false` (boolean, required) - Whether the notification has been deleted by the recipient.
+ `iconurl`: `https://lms.nust.edu.pk/portal/theme/image.php/moove/mod_forum/1778048051/icon` (string, required) - URL to the icon image representing the notification source.
+ `component`: `mod_forum` (string, required) - Moodle component that generated the notification (e.g., 'mod_forum').
+ `eventtype`: `posts` (string, required) - Event type within the component that triggered the notification (e.g., 'posts').
+ `customdata`: `{"cmid":"1272420","instance":"62569","discussionid":"41767"}` (string, required) - JSON-encoded string with additional notification metadata (cmid, instance, discussionid, postid, etc.).


## PopupNotificationsResponse (object)
Response envelope for the popup-notifications endpoint.

### Properties
+ `notifications` (array[Notification], required) - List of popup notifications for the user.
+ `unreadcount`: `1` (number, required) - Total number of unread notifications for the user.


## GetRecentCoursesRequest (object)
Request parameters for retrieving recently accessed courses.

### Properties
+ `limit`: `10` (number, required) - Maximum number of courses to return.


## GetEnrolledCoursesByTimelineRequest (object)
Request parameters for retrieving enrolled courses filtered by timeline classification.

### Properties
+ `offset`: `0` (number, required) - Zero-based pagination offset.
+ `limit`: `50` (number, required) - Maximum number of courses to return.
+ `classification` (enum[string], required) - Timeline classification filter for enrolled courses.
    + `all`
    + `inprogress`
    + `past`
    + `future`
    + `favourites`
    + `hidden`
    + `allincludinghidden`
+ `sort` (enum[string], required) - Field used to sort enrolled course results.
    + `fullname`
    + `shortname`
    + `id`
    + `idnumber`
    + `timeaccess`


## GetCalendarEventsByTimesortRequest (object)
Request parameters for retrieving calendar action events sorted by time.

### Properties
+ `limitnum`: `20` (number, required) - Maximum number of events to return.
+ `timesortfrom`: `0` (number, required) - Only return events with timesort >= this Unix timestamp. Pass 0 for no lower bound.
+ `timesortto` (number, optional) - Only return events with timesort <= this Unix timestamp. Optional.
+ `aftereventid` (number, optional) - Return events whose ID is greater than this value (cursor pagination). Optional.


## GetCalendarEventsByCourseRequest (object)
Request parameters for retrieving calendar action events for a specific course.

### Properties
+ `courseid`: `49906` (number, required) - ID of the course to fetch events for.
+ `timesortfrom` (number, optional) - Only return events with timesort >= this Unix timestamp. Optional.
+ `timesortto` (number, optional) - Only return events with timesort <= this Unix timestamp. Optional.
+ `aftereventid` (number, optional) - Cursor-based pagination — return events after this event ID. Optional.
+ `limitnum` (number, optional) - Maximum number of events to return. Optional.


## GetPopupNotificationsRequest (object)
Request parameters for retrieving popup notifications for a user.

### Properties
+ `useridto`: `123456` (string, required) - ID of the recipient user, passed as a string.
+ `limit`: `20` (number, required) - Maximum number of notifications to return.
+ `offset`: `0` (number, required) - Pagination offset.


